dcterms:description: The IEEE 39-bus system is used to evaluate the performance of the proposed FDIA detection and localization framework, demonstrating its interpretability and robustness.
dcterms:title: IEEE 39-bus system

dcterms:description: PSCAD/EMTDC simulation data is generated to create training and test datasets for evaluating the proposed framework, involving 16500 time-domain simulations.
dcterms:title: PSCAD/EMTDC simulation data

dcterms:description: Kernel Density Estimation (KDE) data from NYISO is used to sample generation and load profiles for the simulations conducted in the study.
dcterms:title: Kernel Density Estimation (KDE) data from NYISO

dcterms:description: Various datasets used for comparison include LSTM, CNN, and GCN models to evaluate the performance of the proposed framework against existing methods.
dcterms:title: Various datasets used for comparison (LSTM, CNN, GCN)
